    "narrative": "The daily offensive outlook for Ghost Ride the WHIP hinges on capitalizing on favorable delivery profiles and park factors. **Trevor Story** (75.93) headlines our slate today; he faces Arrighetti, whose slow delivery cadence creates a massive green light for stolen base attempts, vaulting **Story** into elite territory. Similarly, **Tyler Soderstrom** (72.65) is a high-confidence start against Cecconi. Between the park-adjusted boost and an advantageous R/R platoon, **Soderstrom** is primed to provide necessary thump. Meanwhile, **Vinnie Pasquantino** (67.83) and **Josh Naylor** (66.05) remain focal points of our daily core, benefitting from soft pitching matchups against Hancock and Lugo respectively, which outweighs the minor park penalties associated with their venues.\n\nStrategic benching remains a necessary friction point in managing our game caps. **Alex Freeland** (46.73) was the strongest consideration for the active roster, narrowly missing the cut due to an unfavorable #9 batting position that saps his daily scoring efficiency compared to the high-floor production of **Seiya Suzuki** (60.72) or **Austin Riley** (60.44). We are closely monitoring **Jose Caballero** (41.62); while his speed is an asset, the matchup against Bradish presents a significant risk, as the pitcher's elite ability to hold runners effectively neuters **Caballero**'s primary utility today. We are playing it safe with **Corbin Carroll** (63.85) despite a tough matchup against Imanaga, banking on his elite sprint speed to force an impact regardless of the SP's skill. Keep a close eye on the weather and any late lineup shifts, as **James Wood** (59.70) relies heavily on his #1 spot to provide the value necessary to justify his inclusion over deeper bench options.",
